  "text": "Receiver operating characteristic (ROC) curve analysis was used to identify any cutoff of %D NT-proBNP (baseline -peak) predictive of LV impairment from baseline to 3-, 6-and 12-month follow-up. %D (baseline -peak) NT-proBNP was entered into the ROC curve analysis as a continuous predictive variable. LV impairment from baseline to 3-, 6-and 12-month follow-up was used as a classification variable (target event). LV impairment was defined as a decrease in LVEF of X20% and/or an increase in LVESV of X15% from baseline [CITATION_1] .",
